summary: This is an email chain from July 2019 between FBI personnel and Assistant U.S. Attorneys from the Southern District of New York regarding the shipment of approximately 23 boxes of case records for scanning. The boxes contain materials from two FBI case files related to an investigation, with the shipment being coordinated via FedEx.

keyFacts: The document coordinates the shipment of approximately 23 boxes of case records for scanning, related to an ongoing investigation.
The boxes contain materials from two specific FBI case files: 72-MM-113327 (approximately 2 boxes) and 31E-MM-108062 (the remainder).
The correspondence involves FBI personnel from the VCAC/Human Trafficking squad in New York and Assistant U.S. Attorneys from the Southern District of New York.
The email chain shows procedural coordination for evidence handling in July 2019, with a FedEx tracking number provided.
Multiple email addresses are redacted, indicating standard operational security for law enforcement and prosecutorial communications.
